Perovskite structures were generated using PySPuDS, a custom high-throughput python wrapper to the SPuDS program. SPuDS minimizes the BVM Global Instability Index (GII) to predict perovskite B-O bond lengths and BO6 tilting magnitudes. Morelock et al. showed that GII correlates with the DFT energies of competing Glazer tilts for ternary ABO3 perovskites31, meaning that SPuDS computed ternary perovskite oxide structures lower the optimization expense when used as starting structures for DFT optimization. SPuDS constrains structures with multiple B-sites, i.e., AB0.5B0.5′O3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
